<emphasis id="B9706466BB38C85F7DFDF9DE2A22C83D" box="[185,336,1574,1600]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="246" reason="1">Distribution</emphasis>
and biology.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C04C3F7BB38C85F7CA9F9DF29DBC83C" authorityName="Lafontaine &amp; Ferris &amp; Walsh" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[493,681,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypotrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trifascia">
<emphasis id="B9706466BB38C85F7CA9F9DF29DBC83C" box="[493,681,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Hypotrix trifascia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs from southern Utah and Colorado southward through Arizona, New 
<collectingRegion id="49C07696BB38C85F7F06F9B229EBC819" box="[578,665,1610,1636]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Mexico</collectingRegion>
, and western Texas to northern 
<collectingCountry id="F313F8E4BB38C85F7EBDF9B22F22C819" box="[1017,1104,1610,1636]" name="Mexico" pageId="21" pageNumber="246">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. Collecting dates range from early April to mid-July and early to late September.
</paragraph>
